The source of waitpid is hosted on Github at the
following URL:

  https://github.com/andrea-corbellini/waitpid

The version control system is Git and the latest
source can be fetched using this command:

  $ git clone git://github.com/andrea-corbellini/waitpid.git

This package is using Autotools. The first time
you put your hands on the source, you'll have to
run these commands first:

  $ aclocal
  $ autoconf
  $ autoheader
  $ automake --add-missing
  $ ./configure
  $ make

You need to run all these commands only once.
Afterwards, you can use just `make'.

See `README' for information about bug reporting.
